... Clerics are supposed to be the masters of healing. Necromancers are supposed to be the masters of the dead. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I guess it depends on how you see clerics - as priests of their god, or as healers. If you see them primarily as healers, you are right. But then, why do they need different healers ? Why do they have so much dedication to their gods (Symbols of.. gems of.. and so on) ?<br>
<br>
On the other hand, if you see them mainly as priests of their gods, then the balance should be different. In order not to imbalance the game too strongly, it could start by modifying some of the buff line, and some of the dd spells the clerics do get. Swap them out. Have a cleric of Bertolluxxious (sp ?) use some mean acid or poison blast, rather than the same smite spell as the others (even if it does the same damage). Have the involved players deities have an effect on the buffs..  and so on.<br>
<br>
